           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome back to What I=E2=
=80=99m Hearing, and thanks to those who came to my chat this morning with =
<b>Lucas Shaw</b> at the Bloomberg Screentime conference. Some personal hig=
hlights from the two-day event:<br/><br/></p><ul style=3D"margin:0;color:#0=
00000;font-size:16px;line-height:30px;margin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;list-sty=
le-type:square;mso-special-format:bullet"><li>Comcast=E2=80=99s <b>Brian Ro=
berts</b> appearing to <i>almost</i> say that <b>David Zaslav</b> is doing =
a good job at Warner Discovery before checking himself and instead praising=
 Zaslav for =E2=80=9Cworking really hard.=E2=80=9D</li><br/><li>Live Nation=
=E2=80=99s <b>Michael Rapino</b> saying, =E2=80=9CWe=E2=80=99re a 2 percent=
-margin business, so we must be the dumbest monopoly alive,=E2=80=9D despit=
e the fact that one <i>very Google-able</i> possible indication of a monopo=
ly is when a business is so large and dominant that it can thrive on
small margins that would prevent others from competing.   </li><br/><li>Net=
flix=E2=80=99s <b>Bela Bajaria</b> saying that the company is not intereste=
d in changing its compensation structure while acknowledging that it has ch=
anged its compensation structure in a few recent instances (see below).</li=
><br/><li>Producer <b>Jason Blum</b> attempting to have a serious business =
conversation about the impact of the labor strikes while stuffing his face =
with chicken wings on <i>Hot Ones</i>.</li><br/><li>Analyst <b>Rich Greenfi=
eld</b>=E2=80=99s lilac dress shirt.</li></ul>
